  "texts": [
    "The first step uses the KLD between the GGD feature vectors to select the lens and cluster boundaries.",
    "The second step is also based on the similarity features of frames to locate keyframes.",
    "The method accuracy is experimentally proven to be high.",
    "The shortcoming of the shot-based keyframe-extraction method is that it cannot handle shots with high motion intensity.",
    "It is easy to select too many keyframes when dealing with shots having little motion variation, whereas for shots with more motion variation, the content cannot be adequately described with one or two keyframes."
